Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/dateReceived
Object: Date a registered benefit was received.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/
Object: All Party Parliamentary Group ontology for UK Parliament

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/FinancialBenefit
Object: A financial benefit received by the group where the total value of the benefit from that source exceeds £1500 and the benefit was received on or after the date of the group’s Inaugural Meeting.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/StatusType
Object: Status of an APPG, for example, registered, pending.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/hasRegisteredContact
Object: Relates an APPG to its registered contact. This is normally the Chair of the APPG, therefore a member.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/APPGCategory
Object: A category of APPG, for example one focussed on a country or on a subject area.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/reportedIn
Object: Relates a registered benefit to the financial reporting year it falls into.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/benefitCurrency
Object: The currency the benefit value is expressed in.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/Agent
Object: An agent. The superset of all people and all groups of people.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/Member
Object: A current or former Member of a House.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/RegisteredBenefit
Object: A benefit received by the group from a source other than Parliament where the total value of the benefit from that source exceeds £1500 and the benefit was received on or after the date of the group’s Inaugural Meeting .

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/benefitValue
Object: The value of the registered benefit.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/receivedBenefit
Object: Relates an APPG to a benefit received.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/BenefitInKind
Object: A benefit in kind such as goods or services received by the group where the total value of the benefit from that source exceeds £1500 and the benefit was received on or after the date of the group’s Inaugural Meeting.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/FinancialReportingYear
Object: The year for which an APPG makes its financial report.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/Group
Object: A group of people or a group of groups or a group of people and groups.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/hasSecretariatRole
Object: Relates an external group to an APPG where they are providing secretariat (administrative) services to that APPG.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/hasAPPGCategory
Object: Relates an APPG to its category, such as a country or subject related APPG.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/hasStatusType
Object: Relates an All Party ParliamentaryGroup to its status type.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/appg/hasPublicEnquiryPoint
Object: Relates an APPG to an secondary enquiry point for that APPG. This may be a contact within or outside Parliament.
